  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries. It typically falls under criminal legislation and financial crime statutes. Money laundering involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations with criminal penalties, including fines and imprisonment, for individuals and organizations involved in such activities.",
